1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:02,360
[theme music]

2
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,520
I'm going to sneak out.

3
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,280
You don't need to sneak out

4
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,840
because Mother allowed you to go.

5
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,600
[all] Go, Lord Rueang! Go, Count Sriyot!

6
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:57,400
You can do it, Count Sorasak! Go!

7
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:58,920
Let's walk over there.

8
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,200
All right.

9
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,360
[Dech] <i><font color="white">Karaked.</font></i>

10
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,080
<i><font color="white">Who are you?</font></i>

11
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,640
I truly love her with all my heart.

12
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:14,000
[Phaulkon] <i><font color="white">I swear I will not love
anyone else but her.</font></i>

13
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,200
I'm so excited.

14
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,120
My lady.

15
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,320
-[Champa] I'm coming.
-Please hurry.

16
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:25,960
I'll be very surprised
if you don't follow them.

17
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:32,720
[Prik] Gosh!

18
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,520
Are they dead, Choi?

19
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,960
They were gasping until their last breath.

20
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:40,960
[Prik] Oh, my god.

21
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,400
They are dead, my lady.

22
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,040
[child sobbing]

23
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,040
Prik.

24
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:52,280
[sobbing]

25
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,840
Chuang.

26
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,280
Yes?

27
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:03,160
From now on,
you and Chik will take care of Boon.

28
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,200
Yes, my lady.

29
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,080
Boon, come here.

30
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,640
[Boon sobbing]

31
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,320
[sighs]

32
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:18,640
As for the corpses,

33
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,240
bring them to the temple, Choi.

34
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:23,040
I'll follow you there
to take care of the funeral.

35
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,200
Yes, my lady.

36
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,040
[Choi] Come and help me.

37
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,720
Tie it tighter.

38
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,320
Are there any more sick people?

39
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,960
Yes. There are a lot more, my lady.

40
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,200
It seems like they got the infection
from each other.

41
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,720
Malaria.

42
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,960
[ominous music]

43
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:50,880
[sighs]
It's the same thing as jungle fever.

44
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:54,000
To fight it,
we must get rid of mosquitoes.

45
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,320
[Prik] Hmm...

46
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:00,640
Easier said than done, my lady.

47
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,480
How are you going to do that?

48
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:05,000
I'll show you how it's done, Prik.

49
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,680
I'm not all bark and no bite.

50
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:10,160
Hmm...
I'm telling you that I'm out of this.

51
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,520
What is she talking about?

52
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,320
Fighting with mosquitoes?

53
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,760
[Prik sighs]

54
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,840
[foreboding music]

55
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:34,280
Everyone, follow me.

56
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:40,200
See? This is where the mosquitoes breed.

57
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:44,600
It's where they lay their eggs.
They like standing water.

58
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,160
[servant 1] Huh?

59
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,320
Over there too.

60
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,880
Go see it for yourself.

61
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,360
You don't believe her, do you?

62
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:57,840
Tell me what happens later.

63
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,040
-Let's go, Chuang.
-Yes, my lady.

64
00:05:59,120 --> 00:05:59,960
Yes, my lady.

65
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,440
[Karaked] These broken clay water jars,
bowls, and coconut shells,

66
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,480
you have to dump out the water.
Don't let it sit there.

67
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,480
-Let's dump it out.
-[servant 2] Yes, my lady.

68
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,720
Pin. Yaem.

69
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,640
The way your lady talks is so strange.

70
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:15,600
How do you put up with that?

71
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,080
Strange?

72
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,680
-Say that again.
-[Prik scoffs]

73
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:22,720
Yes.

74
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:25,600
-And you'll know what's up.
-Oh, god.

75
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,480
[Karaked] Turn them over
when they're not in use.

76
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,960
[Karaked sighs]

77
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:36,840
These clay water jars for kitchen use,

78
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,840
who is in charge of them?

79
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,000
[Karaked] Is it you, Prik?

80
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:44,080
[quirky music]

81
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,840
Yes, my lady.

82
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:50,600
Why don't you have lids on them?

83
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,720
Oh, why would I do that?

84
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,320
It's easier to take out the water
if it's open.

85
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,920
Open the lid when you want to use it.

86
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,400
[scoffs]
Why do I have to do that?

87
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,280
That's my order. Only open it when in use.

88
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,960
Close the lid when it's not.
Do you understand?

89
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,360
Ah!

90
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,520
Got it?

91
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:13,760
Fine! I'll be gone with it.
[grunts]

92
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,400
Come on. Get some lids on them.

93
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,480
[servants] Yes, my lady.

94
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,240
-Every one of them.
-Yes, my lady.

95
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:37,680
From now on, everyone has to make sure
that there's no standing water.

96
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,640
You got me?

97
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,960
[servants] Yes, my lady.

98
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,440
[light music]

99
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,280
[soft chuckle]

100
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,680
How was it, Prik?

101
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,800
Look at that long face.

102
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,040
What happened?

103
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,280
She told us to put the lids
on the clay water jars.

104
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,240
Wait.

105
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,600
Don't you do that every day?

106
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,480
I don't, my lady.

107
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,280
Why not?

108
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,480
[both sigh]

109
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:26,200
The dust and dirt
might have mixed in there.

110
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:27,960
[Champa sighs]

111
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,960
Then you use that water to cook for me?

112
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,400
What are you laughing at?

113
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,960
She's laughing at you.

114
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,160
[sighs]
Yes.

115
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:41,440
Oh, well.
You rushed in here to tell on her.

116
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,320
Will you put the lids on from now on?

117
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,000
Yes, my lady.

118
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,960
Lady Champa.

119
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:53,320
The servants are getting sick because
they don't sleep in mosquito nets.

120
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:56,680
They get sick when they are bitten.

121
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,760
Of course, they don't sleep in the nets

122
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,760
because they don't have any.

123
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,280
I'll buy some for them.

124
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,240
[Horathibodi sighs]

125
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,560
Look at her, Dech.

126
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,800
I'm not surprised at all, Father.

127
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,440
Buying mosquito nets for servants.

128
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,680
You have gone truly crazy.

129
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:26,640
[sighs]

130
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:30,040
That's not how masters treat
their servants.

131
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,320
Don't even think about it.

132
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:58,640
[calm music]

133
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,520
[calm music continues]

134
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,760
[gasps]
Ketsurang.

135
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,840
Don't act like you are
in a romantic-comedy movie.

136
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,480
[playful music]

137
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,200
[sighs]

138
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,520
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi</font></i>, here's some cash--

139
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,720
I mean, this is bia
to buy nets for the servants.

140
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,200
Didn't you hear what I just said?

141
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,520
-<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>
-[Dech] I heard you.

142
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,600
And this is what I'm expecting.

143
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,520
I knew that

144
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,960
you would find a way to do it.

145
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:00,160
And I'm the only one

146
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,240
who you can nag

147
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,680
into doing what you want.

148
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,160
[romantic music]

149
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,200
You are so good at reading me.

150
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,760
You're the best.

151
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,800
I'm going back to my chamber now.

152
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,520
It's getting late.

153
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,960
People might misunderstand us
if they see us together.

154
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,320
[theme music]

155
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,760
You're aware of that but still,

156
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,040
you came down here
to find me at this hour.

157
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:11,160
It's just a second.

158
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,320
It's fine.

159
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,840
[sighs]

160
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:16,960
You are not making sense again.

161
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,160
You will get used to it.

162
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,120
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

163
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,760
I'm the one buying the nets.

164
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,720
I will pay for them with my own money.

165
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,840
You should go back to your chamber.

166
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,800
It might look inappropriate for us

167
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,320
to be seen in this situation.

168
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,480
What a gentleman.

169
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,880
[light music]

170
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,440
How much is a net?

171
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:51,240
It costs 200 bia each, my lady.

172
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,960
Then, you put these in bags,
two-hundred each.

173
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,560
And give them to the servants
so they can buy nets for themselves.

174
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,120
You're giving it to everyone?

175
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,680
Of course.

176
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,840
It's not enough, my lady.

177
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:24,120
What about this?
Can I break one baht into bia?

178
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:26,960
Of course, my lady.

179
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,960
Eight fueang is one baht.

180
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,320
One fueang is 800 bia.

181
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:34,400
We can buy four nets with that.

182
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:39,120
One fueang can buy four nets.

183
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:43,480
Then one baht can buy...

184
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,480
thirty-two nets!

185
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:48,360
Wow. That's a lot of nets.

186
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:51,360
In my time, we can barely buy anything
with two baht.

187
00:15:56,360 --> 00:16:00,200
Here. Take these two baht and exchange it

188
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,360
then give it to every servant for me.

189
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:05,880
-Yes, my lady.
-Yes, my lady.

190
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,920
-This is yours. Take it.
-Thank you.

191
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,840
-This one is yours.
-[servant 3] Take it.

192
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,440
Don't thank me.

193
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:17,680
Thank Lady Karaked, not me.

194
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,720
She's over there.

195
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,840
-My lady.
-[Karaked] What is it, Yaem?

196
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,200
It's not enough money, my lady.

197
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:29,840
There are around ten servants
still waiting.

198
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,240
Then, go back and tell them
that I'll give them some more.

199
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:33,800
Yes, my lady.

200
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,200
[clicks tongue]

201
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,920
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

202
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,560
Watch where you're going.

203
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:55,120
I can't see. You're in the way.

204
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,160
Hey.

205
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,040
[laughs]

206
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:05,320
I know you have a lot of money.

207
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,480
But the owner of the house

208
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,920
has to buy things for his servants.

209
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,560
It's fine.

210
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,880
-I--
-My mother is asking for you.

211
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,960
Me?

212
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,080
Yes.

213
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,760
I told you. Who else could it be?

214
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:28,160
Well, it might be someone named Yu.

215
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:34,520
Then let's go. What are you waiting for?

216
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:35,840
Let's go.

217
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,640
Get out of the way, please.

218
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,560
What is this?

219
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,240
Here's the money to buy nets.

220
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:54,920
Two baht.

221
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,800
[light music]

222
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,840
[Champa] Mm.

223
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:17,640
Thank you so much, Lady Champa.

224
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,360
Even though I was awful to you,
the truth is,

225
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,440
I love you, Lady Champa.

226
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:26,080
[scoffs]

227
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,680
Hope this is not going to happen again.

228
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,200
They are my servants,

229
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,160
Mother's and Father's.

230
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,640
We'll take care of them ourselves.

231
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,520
I'll excuse myself
to give the money to Pin and Yaem then.

232
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:53,520
[sighs]

233
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:55,520
Look at her manners.

234
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:59,680
[Champa sighs]
Can we teach her to be a proper lady

235
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,560
in time for the wedding?

236
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:04,840
Please don't rush her about it, Mother.

237
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,360
I feel like

238
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,440
she doesn't want to marry me now.

239
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,600
[sighs]

240
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,880
What about you, son?

241
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:22,320
I'm not so worried about how I feel.

242
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,280
I'm only worried about her feeling.

243
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,920
[foreboding music]

244
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,960
Is there an urgent official matter?

245
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:09,800
No, Lady Nim.

246
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,960
Marquess Kosathibodi called for me.

247
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,160
Lady Chanwad.

248
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,520
Do you have any idea what it is about?

249
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:24,440
I have no idea.

250
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,840
But I don't think it's a serious matter.

251
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:35,200
I met him at the warehouse yesterday.

252
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:38,560
It was late in the afternoon
and he didn't say anything.

253
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:41,720
Please go see him

254
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,520
to find out what this is about.

255
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:58,520
Chanwad.

256
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,400
Have you heard anything about this?

257
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:03,440
When Count Sorasak had a conversation
with Father last night,

258
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:05,200
I was eavesdropping.

259
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,680
Oh, my. That's inappropriate.

260
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,600
Count Surasakorn

261
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,960
conspires with the westerners
to commit fraud.

262
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:16,440
Fraud?

263
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:18,680
Oh my.

264
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,960
Who did they steal money from?

265
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,680
Their own trading company.

266
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:26,920
[gasps]

267
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,040
How did they do that?

268
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:35,240
Those two westerners are working
for the British trading company.

269
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,960
They bought some goods from the Treasury.

270
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,120
[Chanwad] They said
it was for their company.

271
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,560
Constance permitted them.

272
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:46,160
However, they sold the goods
for their own profit.

273
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,640
Is that true, Mr. Phaulkon?

274
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:58,120
Who told you about this, my lord?

275
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,440
Count Sorasak.

276
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:02,000
What did he say?

277
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,240
To tell you the truth,

278
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,680
he said that your British friends,

279
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:10,200
Mr. White and Mr. Burnaby,

280
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:13,200
bought some goods from the Treasury

281
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,920
with your permission.

282
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,960
[Lord Lek] They bought various things

283
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,360
including gold

284
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:24,080
and some sought-after precious stones.

285
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,240
That's what happened.

286
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,520
But they absolutely did
follow the regulation.

287
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,320
Do you realize

288
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:37,240
that they didn't do that for the purpose
of the British trade company

289
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:40,200
but for their own profit?

290
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,240
Is that true?

291
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:46,200
This has caused
great damage to the British

292
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,840
because that was
a significant financial loss.

293
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,560
I'm afraid that

294
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,960
there might be a claim
and then the King will find out.

295
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:57,360
Oh, my god.

296
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:02,360
[sighs deeply]

297
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:07,680
But I told Count Sorasak that
you're definitely not involved in this

298
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:12,280
because I'm certain
that you're truly an honest man.

299
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:15,320
It must be those two foreigners

300
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:18,120
who committed fraud
against their own company.

301
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:24,880
I'm afraid the rumor will be spread out.

302
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,560
Make sure you find ways to prevent it.

303
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,840
Thank you for your kindness, my lord.

304
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:46,280
[foreboding music]

305
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:59,560
I bid my farewell, Lady Nim.

306
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:04,440
As you wish.

307
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:08,400
Was it an important matter?

308
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:11,920
It was someone else's fraud.

309
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:13,960
I wasn't involved.

310
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,560
Then, I'm happy for you.

311
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:19,560
Farewell.

312
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,160
This way, please.

313
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,200
Please come in.

314
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:29,120
[Nim] He is in the main quarter.

315
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:30,520
-Yes.
-Yes.

316
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:32,400
This way, please.

317
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:51,960
Hello, sir.

318
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:54,320
Please wait.

319
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,400
Lord Hora.

320
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,440
Hello.

321
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:09,840
Please excuse me.

322
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:16,680
I am glad you're here.

323
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:19,920
We haven't finished
our last conversation yet.

324
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,960
We were distracted
by all the talk about nets.

325
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,040
Well...

326
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,920
I want to know
whether Constantine Phaulkon

327
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:33,560
is loyal to Marquess Kosathibodi.

328
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,160
That is an odd question.

329
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,920
Why do you think

330
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,560
he is not loyal to him?

331
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:49,200
[Horathibodi] Phaulkon
has been working for him for ten years.

332
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:51,720
Marquess Kosathibodi
trusts and supports him.

333
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:54,960
He introduced him to the King
and made him an official.

334
00:25:56,680 --> 00:26:01,040
Even His Majesty trusts him the most.

335
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:19,320
King Narai trusts him the most?

336
00:26:20,960 --> 00:26:21,960
[gasps]

337
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,760
Is he a good guy or a bad guy?

338
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:26,840
[Dech] Who?

339
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,080
Who?

340
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:35,760
Don't play innocent.

341
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,080
Play innocent?

342
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:41,760
No. I'm not playing anything.

343
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:43,760
Karaked.

344
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:47,400
What you asked was odd just
like my father said.

345
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,040
Why did you ask him that?

346
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,480
It's nothing, <i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

347
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,120
I don't believe it.

348
00:26:58,280 --> 00:26:59,960
[Karaked sighs]

349
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,440
Tell me.

350
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:06,480
What do you know about Count Surasakorn?

351
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,400
What is he like?

352
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:11,760
[foreboding music]

353
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:22,440
I don't know anything.

354
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:24,440
You don't know?

355
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:26,560
Then why did you ask that?

356
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,400
Because I don't know him.

357
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:33,120
So I thought he could be
both good and bad.

358
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:42,560
Why are you interested in this foreigner?

359
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:45,960
Because I argued with him once.

360
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:48,160
He acted mean.

361
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,160
He threatened Mali and her father,

362
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:53,200
but Lord Hora said he is a good man.

363
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,560
His Majesty also thinks the same.

364
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:58,240
That means he has some good in him.

365
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:02,280
That's the truth.

366
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:07,760
Everyone has a good side and a bad side.

367
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:10,160
The important thing is

368
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:13,320
whether the bad side
is harming other people or not.

369
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:16,080
Then when will we know that?

370
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:19,240
[theme music]

371
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:26,160
People can't hide

372
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:30,360
their good or bad deeds for so long.

373
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:49,800
[Karaked's spirit sobbing]

374
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:57,840
[sobbing continues]

375
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,640
Did you hear that?

376
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:06,800
No.

377
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:08,800
You didn't hear anything?

378
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,320
Yes.

379
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:18,240
[sobbing]

380
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,960
[sobbing continues]

381
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:45,360
Your father said Marquess Kosathibodi
loves him like his own son.

382
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,160
Marquess Kosathibodi did say that

383
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:53,920
since Phaulkon can complete
any task he's given.

384
00:29:56,280 --> 00:30:01,160
Even with the King's commands,
he carries them out perfectly.

385
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:21,160
[foreboding music]

386
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,400
[foreboding music continues]

387
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:51,800
[Narai] Today, I will talk about
the fortress construction.

388
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:53,840
Count Surasakorn.

389
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:57,520
I gave you an order to research
on how to build it.

390
00:30:58,240 --> 00:30:59,480
Did you take the action?

391
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:05,520
[Phaulkon] Yes, Your Majesty.

392
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:08,320
Should we build it or not?

393
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:11,040
It should be built, Your Majesty.

394
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:27,040
I have drawn up a plan for the fortress
for you to see.

395
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:29,840
[foreboding music]

396
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:38,560
[foreboding music continues]

397
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:57,760
How excellent.

398
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:01,840
Then supervise the construction
according to this plan.

399
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,680
If you do it well,

400
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:07,240
I will promote you.

401
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:11,200
I'm most grateful
for Your Majesty's kindness.

402
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:17,200
Even if the manual work
can be put to the royal soldiers

403
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,320
who perform unpaid labor,

404
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:21,120
we still have to buy bricks, cement

405
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:23,440
and sugar cane juice
for sealing those bricks.

406
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:30,320
Where could I receive the grant
for the construction, Your Majesty?

407
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:31,840
There.

408
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:33,520
[Narai] Ask Lord Lek.

409
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:39,120
Does Treasury in your control
collect a lot of money, Lek?

410
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:42,560
Then spare me some of it
for the construction, will you?

411
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:47,160
Of course, Your Majesty.

412
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:50,920
[tense music]

413
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:59,280
[tense music continues]

414
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:10,080
I don't agree with
the construction of the fortress.

415
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:13,400
[sighs]
But it is His Majesty's order.

416
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,160
You're right.

417
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:17,520
I know it is the King's order.

418
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:21,360
But it stemmed from you, didn't it?

419
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:23,960
Why didn't you tell him

420
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:26,120
that it shouldn't be built?

421
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:29,960
Who could oppose
the King's decision, my lord?

422
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:33,480
He always has plans to build things.

423
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:35,560
In the last three or four years,

424
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:38,120
he has ordered a palace to be built

425
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:40,200
and also the roads in Lavo.

426
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:43,880
Now it's time to build a fortress.

427
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:46,840
People here are not used
to having a fortress.

428
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:49,120
Do you know why?

429
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:52,120
It makes us feel like we are confined.

430
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:54,960
But we are not actually confined, my lord.

431
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:01,280
Also, there are not that many commoners
in the minor cities

432
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,560
where the fortress will be built.

433
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:06,160
Many of them will be working
for the crown at that time.

434
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,880
[Lord Lek] Therefore,
they might be overworked.

435
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:11,520
They have to make a living
for themselves too.

436
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:14,720
But it has to be done.

437
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:16,440
I take pity on them.

438
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:19,680
Then you have to express your concern
to the King yourself.

439
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:22,200
[tense music]

440
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:39,920
Wait.

441
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:42,600
I'm going to do it.

442
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:46,760
Count Surasakorn.

443
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:50,360
Do warn those two British friends of yours

444
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:52,560
about the fraud against their own company.

445
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:55,200
The British are not stupid.

446
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:59,400
[Lord Lek] It's a serious matter
involving many people.

447
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,520
You can't cover it up.

448
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:04,920
Where there's a fire, there's smoke.

449
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:07,080
And you can't stop smoke

450
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,280
from spreading.

451
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:13,960
Then, you might be drawn into this

452
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:17,720
because you permitted them
to buy those goods.

453
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,160
And at the same time,

454
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:24,280
you were selling goods
to the British company.

455
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,680
That amounts to a lot of money you got.

456
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:32,560
It's over the regulated number of goods.

457
00:35:35,960 --> 00:35:36,800
And you

458
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,560
will end up as a conspirator with them.

459
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,720
What are you waiting for? Go!

460
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:51,880
[servants] Yes.

461
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:55,200
[tense music]

462
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:10,160
[Richard] <i><font color="white">You said he wouldn't know.</font></i>

463
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:12,000
How did he know?

464
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,160
Someone told him.

465
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:20,600
Who?

466
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:23,440
It's Count Sorasak

467
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:26,520
and his father, Earl Phetracha.

468
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:28,960
Earl Phetracha?

469
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:33,760
That means he has a lot of power.
Is that right?

470
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:42,360
He's the head of the Royal Elephant Corps.

471
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:49,840
His mother is
one of King Narai's two wet nurses.

472
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:53,760
His younger sister is

473
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:59,440
the main concubine of the King himself.

474
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:05,440
He doesn't like me at all.

475
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:11,560
[man 1 yells]

476
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:12,760
[thwacks]

477
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:15,720
EXTINGUISH THE LAMPS

478
00:37:18,160 --> 00:37:19,880
-[man 2 yells]
-[thwacking]

479
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:23,440
SERPENT TWISTS ITS TAIL

480
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,600
HANUMAN THE MONKEY KING
PRESENTS THE RING

481
00:37:36,040 --> 00:37:37,560
BREAK THE ELEPHANT'S TUSKS

482
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:40,840
LIFTING THE SUMERU MOUNTAIN

483
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:43,320
[man 3 thuds]

484
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:51,200
[thwacks]

485
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:57,120
[action music]

486
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,280
[man 4 groans]

487
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:11,440
[elephant roars]

488
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,800
[foreboding music]

489
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,200
What are you thinking about, Father?

490
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:47,920
Count Surasakorn.

491
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:52,840
I couldn't loathe him more
than I have had.

492
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:55,280
I can't figure out

493
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:59,880
how he got such a young
and beautiful wife either, Father.

494
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:01,480
They are both westerners, that's why.

495
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:03,680
Not exactly, Father.

496
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,880
She is part Indian and part Japanese.

497
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:09,160
Is she beautiful?

498
00:39:09,400 --> 00:39:10,320
[sighs]

499
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:11,880
Stunning.

500
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,280
That Constance is lucky.

501
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:17,680
He is untrustworthy.

502
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:21,280
I'm afraid he might convince King Narai

503
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:25,360
to convert.

504
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:27,240
King Narai is wise.

505
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:29,880
He wouldn't be so gullible to convert.

506
00:39:31,920 --> 00:39:33,480
[elephant trumpets]

507
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:37,520
Hey, Mahout.

508
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:41,120
What are you doing to the male elephant?
Why is he crying out so loud?

509
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,400
[elephant moaning]

510
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:45,800
It might be Kwan, the female elephant.
She's injured.

511
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:49,760
I'll see if I can find some medicine
for her.

512
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:52,520
Hey, Duea.

513
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,200
What happened when you told Lord Lek

514
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:58,560
about how Constance is committing fraud?

515
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:00,760
[sighs]

516
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:02,040
When I told him,

517
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:05,120
he just sat there listening.

518
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,120
He didn't say anything?

519
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:08,320
He did, Father.

520
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:10,640
He said...

521
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:14,520
That man is hard-working and determined.

522
00:40:15,400 --> 00:40:17,240
He works to serve King Narai.

523
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,920
He's also smart and quick-witted.

524
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,480
I don't think he could have done that

525
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,520
to someone he respects
like his own father, Duea.

526
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:28,160
I knew it.

527
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:32,440
That Constance must have given him
so many gifts.

528
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:36,040
Lord Lek loves gifts so much, you know?

529
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:39,400
There's such a rumor, Father.

530
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:46,360
That foreigner just knows
how to gain favor with him.

531
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:53,520
[calm music]

532
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,920
[calm music continues]

533
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:11,280
Chanwad.

534
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:14,360
How come we are having
many guests visiting today?

535
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:18,880
The officials of administrative
departments are here to see Father.

536
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:23,400
He asked me to prepare food for them
after they finish talking.

537
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,520
I see. They came from the minor cities.

538
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:29,160
They could have brought along
a lot of gifts.

539
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:32,200
[sighs]
Get someone to welcome them.

540
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,120
I'll take care of the food myself.

541
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:35,920
Yes, Mother.

542
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:38,120
-Boon. Muern.
-Yes, my lady.

543
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:40,200
-Follow me to the kitchen.
-Yes, my lady.

544
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:49,560
Are you Lady Chanwad?

545
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:51,040
Yes, my lord.

546
00:41:51,960 --> 00:41:53,480
Did you bring anything along?

547
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,440
I'll get some servants to carry it.

548
00:41:56,240 --> 00:41:57,200
No, my lady.

549
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:59,960
I only have something to talk about
with your father.

550
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:03,080
Duang.

551
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:07,800
-[Chanwad] You two, follow me.
-This way, please.

552
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:08,800
[servants] Yes, my lady.

553
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:15,760
What happened?

554
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:18,520
They didn't bring anything.

555
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:21,040
What? How unusual.

556
00:42:22,880 --> 00:42:24,960
How do they act
with such uncustomary behavior?

557
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:28,840
[Nim] They should bring something
when they are visiting people's houses.

558
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:31,160
Then why are they here?

559
00:42:32,280 --> 00:42:34,240
I would like to ask you for a favor.

560
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:36,560
What is it?

561
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:39,080
It's about the construction
of the fortress, my lord.

562
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:40,680
What about it?

563
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:44,560
Building a large and durable fortress
according to the King's wishes

564
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:47,040
would require a lot of labor

565
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:51,280
and take a long period of time.

566
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:55,880
It would also require
long-lasting building tools

567
00:42:56,800 --> 00:43:01,080
which we need to find more of
since we don't have any of them.

568
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:03,960
Families would be without
the head of the house.

569
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:07,280
Who would find food to support them?

570
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:08,680
Hey.
[chuckles]

571
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:13,200
I don't see them finding food
to feed their family anyway.

572
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:16,840
All they do is gamble
and drink, don't they?

573
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:21,640
[sighs]
Every one of them.

574
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:24,320
I only see the women of the house
sweating it out of the work.

575
00:43:25,320 --> 00:43:26,760
They clear out thickets.

576
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:28,680
Fill up the water jar
and prepare for food.

577
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:31,280
[sighs]
The men like you

578
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:33,680
are always in gambling dens.

579
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:39,240
It is not that I don't hear what you said.

580
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:42,200
I don't agree with
His Majesty's decision either

581
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:44,200
because

582
00:43:44,760 --> 00:43:47,680
we are not used to having a fortress.

583
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:50,920
I think

584
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:53,240
it would make us feel like
we are imprisoned.

585
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,200
I'm also thinking about

586
00:43:57,440 --> 00:43:59,520
telling him what I told you earlier.

587
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:01,880
I don't know what he would think.

588
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:04,480
[Lord Lek] You all know that

589
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:09,360
if he decides to do something,
nobody can change his mind.

590
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:12,280
It's all because that westerner
told His Majesty so, isn't it?

591
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:14,560
[tuts]
Be careful what you say.

592
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:18,520
He can come to my house anytime.

593
00:44:20,960 --> 00:44:23,120
Why would he trust such foreigner

594
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:25,240
more than his own people?

595
00:44:25,640 --> 00:44:27,160
His Majesty has his reasons.

596
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:29,040
That man is capable of many things.

597
00:44:29,680 --> 00:44:31,520
All of which King Narai
doesn't know about.

598
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:35,880
It makes him excited.

599
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:39,160
People have their good and bad side.

600
00:44:39,760 --> 00:44:42,240
Don't believe in anything
you haven't witnessed yourself.

601
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:43,920
-Yes, my lord.
-Yes, my lord.

602
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:46,440
Don't let anyone know about

603
00:44:47,320 --> 00:44:48,960
what we discussed today.

604
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:51,320
Or else you will be in serious trouble.

605
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:53,960
[Lord Lek] I will be fine

606
00:44:54,760 --> 00:44:56,560
since I'm one of His Majesty's favorites.

607
00:44:57,240 --> 00:44:58,680
Do you understand?

608
00:44:59,120 --> 00:45:00,280
Yes, my lord.

609
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:02,440
We will keep it a secret forever.

610
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:05,960
Now that we are done talking.
You can leave.

611
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:08,600
[foreboding music]

612
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:14,960
What is it?

613
00:45:23,080 --> 00:45:26,640
[man 5] This is 50 chang
that we have gathered for you.

614
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:40,320
It's to show our support for you
advising against the King's wish.

615
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:44,200
All right. You can go now.

616
00:45:44,560 --> 00:45:46,040
-Farewell.
-Farewell.

617
00:45:51,400 --> 00:45:53,400
[foreboding music]

618
00:45:58,720 --> 00:46:00,720
[foreboding music continues]

619
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:14,600
-[Lord Lek] Put this in my room
-[servant 4] Yes, my lord.

620
00:46:22,640 --> 00:46:23,800
Father.

621
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:26,680
If this gets to King Narai,

622
00:46:27,040 --> 00:46:29,400
wouldn't it look like you took a bribe?

623
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:32,040
Oh, that money?

624
00:46:33,240 --> 00:46:35,320
[sighs]
It's not exactly a bribe

625
00:46:36,040 --> 00:46:38,800
since I was planning to advise against
the construction to the King

626
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:40,040
with or without the money.

627
00:46:42,640 --> 00:46:43,520
But...

628
00:46:44,880 --> 00:46:45,720
Chanwad.

629
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:49,560
Don't worry about it.
It's not that much money.

630
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:52,720
[sighs]
Do you know

631
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:56,200
how much money other masters receive
from servants in their protection?

632
00:47:00,360 --> 00:47:02,800
People think it's normal to do this.

633
00:47:04,560 --> 00:47:06,320
You don't have to worry about it.

634
00:47:12,080 --> 00:47:13,240
[Chanwad] But Mother,

635
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:15,720
I've heard people talking about our house.

636
00:47:17,120 --> 00:47:18,120
They said, for example,

637
00:47:18,480 --> 00:47:20,760
that the trays with a pedestal for fruits
people bought from us--

638
00:47:21,400 --> 00:47:22,440
[Nim] Chanwad.

639
00:47:22,760 --> 00:47:25,840
Those trays came with the fruits.
They were given to your father as gifts.

640
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:28,560
How could we keep all of them?

641
00:47:29,760 --> 00:47:32,080
Some of them were made of gold and silver.

642
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:34,960
That's because they respect him so much.

643
00:47:35,440 --> 00:47:36,920
Don't make a fuss about it.

644
00:47:42,200 --> 00:47:44,360
Boon, Muern, follow me.

645
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:55,040
There is nothing to worry about, Chanwad.

646
00:47:56,640 --> 00:47:57,480
Yes, Father.

647
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:01,520
[foreboding music]

648
