Why do you not feel well?

797
00:57:43,880 --> 00:57:44,720
I...

798
00:57:46,960 --> 00:57:48,560
It's my pregnancy.

799
00:57:50,760 --> 00:57:53,000
I want to ask my mother for advice

800
00:57:53,840 --> 00:57:55,520
on what I should and shouldn't do.

801
00:57:57,680 --> 00:58:00,080
If I didn't have to stay
and oversee the construction,

802
00:58:00,960 --> 00:58:02,400
I would go with you.

803
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:22,360
I promise it will not be long

804
00:58:23,240 --> 00:58:24,400
until I come back.

805
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:28,320
[foreboding music]

806
00:58:35,920 --> 00:58:37,920
[foreboding music continues]

807
00:58:44,640 --> 00:58:46,240
Take care of yourself

808
00:58:47,760 --> 00:58:48,760
and our baby,

809
00:58:50,960 --> 00:58:51,960
Tong Guyomar.

810
00:58:56,520 --> 00:58:57,520
Yes, my lord.

811
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:02,000
[calm music]

812
00:59:15,320 --> 00:59:17,320
[calm music continues]

813
00:59:42,720 --> 00:59:44,200
What did you say?

814
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:53,800
[Lord Lek] I think fortresses

815
00:59:54,320 --> 00:59:56,600
are not in our tradition.

816
00:59:57,320 --> 00:59:59,120
People are not used to them.

817
00:59:59,800 --> 01:00:01,400
It would be like we are confined.

818
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:03,320
The enemy can take over them more easily.

819
01:00:04,200 --> 01:00:06,160
It's also harder to drive them out.

820
01:00:06,720 --> 01:00:07,600
Hey.

821
01:00:08,440 --> 01:00:10,680
Lord Lek, I already gave my order.

822
01:00:11,160 --> 01:00:13,760
It's not so important
that it can't be changed.

823
01:00:14,560 --> 01:00:16,800
Please do not waste money
for no apparent reason, Your Majesty.

824
01:00:17,600 --> 01:00:19,560
Don't you want to give me the money?

825
01:00:20,160 --> 01:00:21,280
No, Your Majesty.

826
01:00:22,040 --> 01:00:23,680
The money is yours.

827
01:00:24,640 --> 01:00:26,640
You can use it the way you see fit,

828
01:00:27,920 --> 01:00:29,840
but using it for the fortress

829
01:00:31,080 --> 01:00:32,560
could end up being abandoned.

830
01:00:33,360 --> 01:00:35,520
Did you just insult me?

831
01:00:39,320 --> 01:00:41,720
When they are attacked or taken over,

832
01:00:43,160 --> 01:00:46,120
it will give a stronghold for the enemy.

833
01:00:53,040 --> 01:00:53,960
Lek.

834
01:00:55,160 --> 01:00:57,160
[Narai] Tell me the truth.

835
01:00:58,200 --> 01:01:01,680
Why do you advise against the fortress?

836
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:06,800
For the reason I have just said,
Your Majesty.

837
01:01:08,040 --> 01:01:09,280
You don't want to spend the money?

838
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:12,760
I shouldn't feel anything about it

839
01:01:13,240 --> 01:01:14,360
because it's all yours.

840
01:01:15,120 --> 01:01:17,240
Isn't it because you accepted a bribe

841
01:01:18,400 --> 01:01:21,200
from those who do not want
the fortress to be built, Lek?

842
01:01:22,960 --> 01:01:24,040
No, Your Majesty.

843
01:01:25,560 --> 01:01:28,520
I didn't take bribes from anyone.

844
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:31,400
I will ask you again.

845
01:01:34,040 --> 01:01:35,760
Did you take bribes

846
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:39,160
from those who don't want
the fortress to be built?

847
01:01:39,880 --> 01:01:41,080
No, Your Majesty.

848
01:01:42,800 --> 01:01:45,400
Again, Lek.

849
01:01:45,960 --> 01:01:47,560
Answer me again!

850
01:01:55,400 --> 01:01:58,520
I stand behind my words, Your Majesty.

851
01:01:59,440 --> 01:02:01,200
Everyone, out.

852
01:02:01,400 --> 01:02:03,400
[foreboding music]

853
01:02:07,960 --> 01:02:09,600
You stay, Lek.

854
01:02:40,200 --> 01:02:43,640
My lady, don't run. You will fall.

855
01:02:47,560 --> 01:02:48,920
[Pin and Yaem] My lady.

856
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:51,120
What? Stop calling me.

857
01:02:51,440 --> 01:02:52,360
My tummy hurts.

858
01:02:52,440 --> 01:02:53,960
[both] Take medicine.

859
01:02:54,560 --> 01:02:56,120
I mean I need to poop.

860
01:02:56,320 --> 01:02:57,360
[both] Privy?

861
01:02:57,440 --> 01:02:58,400
Yes.

862
01:02:58,920 --> 01:02:59,880
[Karaked groans]

863
01:02:59,960 --> 01:03:02,720
Oh, no. Yaem, let's follow her.

864
01:03:03,880 --> 01:03:05,840
-Wait.
-Wait. Get some cloth.

865
01:03:06,560 --> 01:03:07,440
That's not enough.

866
01:03:07,640 --> 01:03:10,600
-Make sure to buy all of what I said.
- [servant 5] Yes.

867
01:03:15,480 --> 01:03:16,360
[Chuang] Hey.

868
01:03:16,800 --> 01:03:18,280
Lady Karaked.

869
01:03:18,360 --> 01:03:20,720
I was about to come and see you
at your quarter.

870
01:03:21,000 --> 01:03:21,840
What is it?

871
01:03:21,920 --> 01:03:24,920
There's a foreign lady
waiting to see you at the pier.

872
01:03:28,120 --> 01:03:29,480
[both] My lady.

873
01:03:30,160 --> 01:03:31,240
-What?
-[Yaem] Pin.

874
01:03:32,880 --> 01:03:34,440
-Chuang.
-What?

875
01:03:34,520 --> 01:03:35,840
You will get slapped.

876
01:03:35,920 --> 01:03:37,880
Don't you know she's going to the privy?

877
01:03:37,960 --> 01:03:39,960
-Let's go, my lady. Go straight.
-Let's go, my lady.

878
01:03:40,120 --> 01:03:41,840
What about the foreign lady?

879
01:03:42,520 --> 01:03:43,880
Yes, you're right.

880
01:03:44,440 --> 01:03:47,320
Pin. Yaem.
You shouldn't be so alarmed by that.

881
01:03:56,360 --> 01:04:00,440
This is Tong Guyomar,
Count Surasakorn's wife.

882
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:04,160
[Champa] Oh.

883
01:04:05,360 --> 01:04:06,680
That's very kind of you.

884
01:04:08,080 --> 01:04:08,920
[Champa] Well.

885
01:04:09,960 --> 01:04:14,120
Do you have an urgent matter with Karaked?

886
01:04:15,800 --> 01:04:16,760
Yes, my lady.

887
01:04:22,640 --> 01:04:26,280
[Mali] May I be excused
for taking her to talk downstairs?

888
01:04:26,360 --> 01:04:27,240
Sure.

889
01:04:28,560 --> 01:04:29,480
Let's go, Mali.

890
01:04:44,120 --> 01:04:46,280
She's a human being like us.

891
01:04:51,040 --> 01:04:52,040
[Prik] Hmm...

892
01:04:53,400 --> 01:04:55,200
Look at the way she dresses.

893
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:59,040
Do you think she ever trips on
her own hem, my lady?

894
01:05:00,640 --> 01:05:02,280
Do you want to dress like her?

895
01:05:02,560 --> 01:05:04,120
-[Prik] Gosh!
-So, you can see for yourself.

896
01:05:04,400 --> 01:05:05,240
[gasps]

897
01:05:06,040 --> 01:05:08,320
That would be hideous.

898
01:05:09,440 --> 01:05:11,440
[quirky music]

899
01:05:15,640 --> 01:05:17,640
[light music]

900
01:05:26,280 --> 01:05:28,480
I'm five months pregnant.

901
01:05:29,880 --> 01:05:30,760
Really?

902
01:05:31,360 --> 01:05:33,160
-Oh?
-See?

903
01:05:36,920 --> 01:05:38,880
[Karaked giggling]

904
01:05:39,840 --> 01:05:41,040
Congratulations.

905
01:05:42,600 --> 01:05:43,560
[Mali] Thank you.

906
01:05:48,080 --> 01:05:50,080
Did you come all the way here
to tell me this?

907
01:05:50,920 --> 01:05:52,080
There's something else.

908
01:05:57,240 --> 01:05:58,160
Tell me.

909
01:05:59,200 --> 01:06:00,360
I have a warning.

910
01:06:02,120 --> 01:06:03,320
A couple of days ago,

911
01:06:03,840 --> 01:06:07,920
I heard my husband
talking to his friends who do trading.

912
01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:11,480
They talked about Marquess Kosathibodi.

913
01:06:12,520 --> 01:06:13,560
I couldn't hear it very well.

914
01:06:15,560 --> 01:06:17,760
But I don't think it's a good thing.

915
01:06:19,520 --> 01:06:21,800
Can you warn him?

916
01:06:23,560 --> 01:06:24,680
Oh, no.

917
01:06:26,040 --> 01:06:27,560
It's getting closer.

918
01:06:28,560 --> 01:06:30,040
[professor] King Narai was furious

919
01:06:30,200 --> 01:06:33,120
that Duke Kosathibodi denied
any wrongdoing.

920
01:06:34,560 --> 01:06:38,720
The King ordered him to be flogged

921
01:06:38,800 --> 01:06:40,680
and that eventually took his life.

922
01:06:44,360 --> 01:06:46,160
What is getting close, Karaked?

923
01:06:50,200 --> 01:06:52,320
[laughs]
It's nothing.

924
01:06:53,040 --> 01:06:54,040
You can continue.

925
01:06:55,360 --> 01:06:58,240
I'm afraid it might be serious

926
01:07:00,760 --> 01:07:02,040
and dangerous.

927
01:07:07,840 --> 01:07:09,640
[Karaked sighs]

928
01:07:10,280 --> 01:07:11,800
It really is.

929
01:07:16,320 --> 01:07:17,560
What do you know?

930
01:07:23,480 --> 01:07:26,200
I only know from
what you just told me, Tong Guyomar.

931
01:07:28,080 --> 01:07:31,680
You know more than I do, don't you?
That's why you are here.

932
01:07:32,360 --> 01:07:34,840
Is this not enough for you, Karaked?

933
01:07:37,400 --> 01:07:39,200
You are smart.

934
01:07:40,560 --> 01:07:42,880
You usually predict
what's going to happen correctly.

935
01:07:50,600 --> 01:07:52,760
I have to go, Karaked.

936
01:07:52,920 --> 01:07:54,840
My helpers might find it suspicious

937
01:07:55,840 --> 01:07:57,120
if I leave home for too long.

938
01:07:58,320 --> 01:07:59,400
I'm leaving then.

939
01:08:04,600 --> 01:08:06,640
Good luck, Mali.

940
01:08:22,840 --> 01:08:23,760
Mali.

941
01:08:26,560 --> 01:08:28,320
I just want to tell you this.

942
01:08:29,680 --> 01:08:31,240
I am still the same old Mali.

943
01:08:32,800 --> 01:08:33,760
It's just that...

944
01:08:36,120 --> 01:08:37,080
It's just that what?

945
01:08:40,800 --> 01:08:41,800
[soft chuckle]

946
01:08:47,680 --> 01:08:49,360
Let me see you off at the pier.

947
01:08:50,560 --> 01:08:51,520
Okay.

948
01:08:58,360 --> 01:09:00,360
[foreboding music]

949
01:09:07,840 --> 01:09:09,840
[ominous music]

950
01:09:24,880 --> 01:09:26,880
[ominous music continues]

951
01:09:33,000 --> 01:09:34,520
My lady.

952
01:09:37,160 --> 01:09:38,680
Are you waiting for Lord Dech?

953
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:40,800
Yes.

954
01:09:41,840 --> 01:09:44,200
Do you know why he hasn't come back?

955
01:09:44,640 --> 01:09:48,480
I'm here to tell you
that he didn't take the boat.

956
01:09:48,560 --> 01:09:49,520
What?

957
01:10:02,320 --> 01:10:04,080
-Give him some water.
-Yes, my lord.

958
01:10:09,720 --> 01:10:11,080
[Pin] My lord.

959
01:10:15,800 --> 01:10:16,920
What is it, Pin?

960
01:10:17,000 --> 01:10:18,320
It's my lady.

961
01:10:18,640 --> 01:10:21,320
She has been waiting for you
all afternoon.

962
01:10:21,880 --> 01:10:22,840
What is it about?

963
01:10:23,680 --> 01:10:25,120
I don't know, my lord.

964
01:10:25,760 --> 01:10:26,960
Where is she?

965
01:10:27,400 --> 01:10:29,880
She is waiting for you at the pier.

966
01:10:32,720 --> 01:10:33,840
Pin.

967
01:10:34,920 --> 01:10:36,320
What's with you, Choi?

968
01:10:36,920 --> 01:10:37,760
[Choi] What's going on?

969
01:10:38,720 --> 01:10:39,880
I don't know either.

970
01:10:40,360 --> 01:10:44,400
My lady paced back and forth.
Then she wrote something down.

971
01:10:44,480 --> 01:10:47,840
Then, she paced back and forth
and looked over to the pier.

972
01:10:48,240 --> 01:10:49,600
Then, she wrote down again and

973
01:10:49,680 --> 01:10:51,560
-Paced back and forth?
-...paced back and forth.

974
01:10:51,640 --> 01:10:53,400
What? How did you know that?

975
01:10:54,240 --> 01:10:55,120
[sighs]

976
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:58,480
You haven't answered me.
Where are you going?

977
01:10:58,560 --> 01:11:00,040
I'm going to pick up elephant dung.

978
01:11:01,080 --> 01:11:03,080
[calm music]

979
01:11:14,400 --> 01:11:16,400
[calm music continues]

980
01:11:18,360 --> 01:11:19,680
Have some desserts,<i><font color="white"> Khun Pi</font></i>.

981
01:11:22,120 --> 01:11:23,680
Tell me what's going on.

982
01:11:26,480 --> 01:11:28,360
Mali came to see me today

983
01:11:28,960 --> 01:11:30,760
to tell me something important.

984
01:11:37,360 --> 01:11:38,320
Prik.

985
01:11:39,480 --> 01:11:40,320
Yes, my lady.

986
01:11:43,240 --> 01:11:45,240
[quirky music]

987
01:11:50,600 --> 01:11:52,120
What are they talking about?

988
01:11:52,200 --> 01:11:53,600
[Prik] Mm-hm!

989
01:11:54,040 --> 01:11:55,480
I want to know too.

990
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:58,280
Hey!
[laughs]

991
01:11:58,360 --> 01:11:59,360
My lady.

992
01:12:03,880 --> 01:12:06,480
I'm worried about Lord Lek.

993
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:11,320
What do you think is going to happen next?

994
01:12:13,160 --> 01:12:14,000
You can tell me.

995
01:12:19,640 --> 01:12:21,640
[foreboding music]

996
01:12:30,240 --> 01:12:32,240
[foreboding music continues]

997
01:12:45,200 --> 01:12:47,200
[tense music]

998
01:12:56,600 --> 01:12:57,440
[Narai] Lek.

999
01:13:03,840 --> 01:13:04,720
Your Majesty.

1000
01:13:06,200 --> 01:13:08,320
I will ask you one last time.

1001
01:13:10,560 --> 01:13:12,960
Are you standing by your answer?

1002
01:13:19,600 --> 01:13:20,560
What is it?

1003
01:13:23,920 --> 01:13:25,000
I am, Your Majesty.

1004
01:13:40,480 --> 01:13:41,560
You are my friend,

1005
01:13:44,160 --> 01:13:45,160
my brother,

1006
01:13:46,920 --> 01:13:47,920
my sibling.

1007
01:13:51,520 --> 01:13:54,560
Your mother also breastfed me.

1008
01:13:58,800 --> 01:14:00,400
We studied together.

1009
01:14:03,480 --> 01:14:04,640
We ate together.

1010
01:14:07,320 --> 01:14:08,720
We played together.

1011
01:14:11,440 --> 01:14:12,840
We fought side by side.

1012
01:14:15,760 --> 01:14:17,080
We worked together.

1013
01:14:21,440 --> 01:14:24,000
I love you like you are my blood brother,

1014
01:14:27,480 --> 01:14:29,480
like we came out of the same womb.

1015
01:14:33,680 --> 01:14:35,040
Have you known that?

1016
01:14:36,800 --> 01:14:38,320
I have, Your Majesty.

1017
01:14:40,920 --> 01:14:41,840
[chuckles]

1018
01:14:44,560 --> 01:14:45,680
All right.

1019
01:14:48,280 --> 01:14:49,560
Know that

1020
01:14:53,040 --> 01:14:55,280
it will be like that forever.

1021
01:14:56,240 --> 01:14:58,240
[dramatic music]

1022
01:15:15,840 --> 01:15:17,840
[dramatic music continues]

1023
01:15:29,960 --> 01:15:30,800
You can go now.

1024
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:37,600
Go back to Ayutthaya tonight.

1025
01:15:37,680 --> 01:15:39,680
[tense music]

1026
01:15:58,320 --> 01:15:59,360
[Karaked sighs]

1027
01:15:59,440 --> 01:16:03,360
I have a feeling
that Lord Lek is in danger.

1028
01:16:04,440 --> 01:16:06,360
[Karaked] I don't know how

1029
01:16:07,040 --> 01:16:11,560
but I feel like it's related
to Count Surasakorn.

1030
01:16:12,040 --> 01:16:13,120
I knew it.

1031
01:16:16,520 --> 01:16:18,640
How is it related to him?

1032
01:16:20,960 --> 01:16:23,040
It might be about trading.

1033
01:16:24,280 --> 01:16:25,280
I don't think so.

1034
01:16:27,120 --> 01:16:30,640
Lord Lek likes that westerner so much.

1035
01:16:31,680 --> 01:16:33,840
He admires him for his excellent trading.

1036
01:16:42,400 --> 01:16:44,600
[rooster crows]

1037
01:17:02,160 --> 01:17:03,000
Duang.

1038
01:17:03,360 --> 01:17:04,480
His lordship is...

1039
01:17:08,360 --> 01:17:10,360
[foreboding music]

1040
01:17:22,960 --> 01:17:24,080
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

1041
01:17:27,200 --> 01:17:30,120
When did you come back from Lavo, Father?

1042
01:17:40,520 --> 01:17:41,760
-Choi.
-Yes, my lord.

1043
01:17:46,760 --> 01:17:48,560
I'm going to Lord Lek's house.

1044
01:17:49,680 --> 01:17:50,560
Okay.

1045
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:53,560
On the way there,
go see Earl Wisut Sunthorn

1046
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:55,040
to inform him about this.

1047
01:17:55,360 --> 01:17:56,280
Yes, Father.

1048
01:17:57,160 --> 01:17:58,280
-Choi.
-Yes, my lord.

1049
01:17:59,120 --> 01:18:02,040
You go and take Earl Wisut Sunthorn
to Lord Lek's house.

1050
01:18:04,440 --> 01:18:05,640
I'm going to pick up Lord Rueang.

1051
01:18:05,960 --> 01:18:06,800
Yes, my lord.

1052
01:18:09,480 --> 01:18:10,680
[Karaked] What about me?

1053
01:18:12,960 --> 01:18:13,840
You stay here.

1054
01:18:14,480 --> 01:18:16,120
[sighs]
Again?

1055
01:18:18,960 --> 01:18:21,240
I mean all the time, Lord Hora.

1056
01:18:22,120 --> 01:18:23,160
Okay.

1057
01:18:33,520 --> 01:18:35,520
[calm music]

1058
01:18:42,600 --> 01:18:44,200
It's pumpkin in coconut milk.

1059
01:18:56,120 --> 01:18:57,560
[sighs]

1060
01:18:58,280 --> 01:19:01,200
His Majesty asked about the money
three times.

1061
01:19:03,240 --> 01:19:04,240
I didn't answer him.

1062
01:19:05,440 --> 01:19:07,040
[Lord Lek] He was probably bluffing me.

1063
01:19:07,960 --> 01:19:09,920
Those in administrative departments
would not sell me out

1064
01:19:11,040 --> 01:19:13,160
because they know
they would end up guilty too.

1065
01:19:22,560 --> 01:19:23,640
My lord.

1066
01:19:24,640 --> 01:19:26,640
[suspenseful music]

1067
01:19:31,200 --> 01:19:33,840
His Majesty ordered you
to be taken away at this moment, my lord.

1068
01:19:39,360 --> 01:19:40,320
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

1069
01:19:46,960 --> 01:19:48,080
[sighs]

1070
01:19:53,120 --> 01:19:55,520
Why do you keep sighing?

1071
01:19:56,120 --> 01:19:58,960
Whatever happens, happens.

1072
01:20:00,640 --> 01:20:02,920
Whatever happens, happens.

1073
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:05,880
[laughs]
You're right, Pin.

1074
01:20:05,960 --> 01:20:07,440
How did you come up with that?

1075
01:20:07,520 --> 01:20:08,480
That's so cool.

1076
01:20:10,680 --> 01:20:12,880
You said it once, my lady.

1077
01:20:15,400 --> 01:20:17,000
Oh.
[clicks tongue]

1078
01:20:17,560 --> 01:20:20,080
That might be true because...

1079
01:20:21,920 --> 01:20:23,280
Because of what?

1080
01:20:26,000 --> 01:20:28,000
[somber music]

1081
01:20:40,080 --> 01:20:40,920
[Karaked sighs]

1082
01:20:42,240 --> 01:20:44,800
Because that is what
the people I come from say.

1083
01:20:46,520 --> 01:20:48,240
Do you mean Song Kwae?

1084
01:20:49,760 --> 01:20:50,760
No.

1085
01:20:52,080 --> 01:20:53,600
Not Song Kwae.

1086
01:20:55,840 --> 01:20:56,720
[sighs]

1087
01:20:59,240 --> 01:21:00,880
[sighs deeply]

1088
01:21:08,440 --> 01:21:11,080
Didn't they say why, Lady Nim?

1089
01:21:11,760 --> 01:21:13,280
[sobbing]
They did not, Pan.

1090
01:21:14,240 --> 01:21:16,280
They just took him.

1091
01:21:17,680 --> 01:21:18,680
[sighs]

1092
01:21:21,120 --> 01:21:22,800
They should have said something.

1093
01:21:23,760 --> 01:21:26,040
Father is a high-ranking official.

1094
01:21:27,760 --> 01:21:29,680
They only said
that it was the King's order.

1095
01:21:30,840 --> 01:21:35,920
What can I do
to find out how my father is doing?

1096
01:21:37,840 --> 01:21:39,680
That would be so difficult, Chanwad.

1097
01:21:41,480 --> 01:21:43,120
[Lord Pan] When it comes
to the King's order,

1098
01:21:44,280 --> 01:21:46,360
the people who took your father

1099
01:21:48,320 --> 01:21:50,120
must be the disciplinary officers

1100
01:21:51,120 --> 01:21:52,720
from the Royal Police Force.

1101
01:21:53,920 --> 01:21:55,640
They receive orders directly
from the King.

1102
01:21:59,040 --> 01:22:00,760
[sobbing]

1103
01:22:00,840 --> 01:22:04,400
Then what can I do?

1104
01:22:05,680 --> 01:22:06,760
[sighs]

1105
01:22:12,920 --> 01:22:14,360
-[Chanwad sniffles]
-Lady Chanwad.

1106
01:22:16,560 --> 01:22:18,520
[Lord Rueang] I have a friend
in the Royal Police force.

1107
01:22:19,920 --> 01:22:21,440
I can ask him about it.

1108
01:22:23,440 --> 01:22:25,840
Please don't be saddened
before anything happens.

1109
01:22:27,640 --> 01:22:29,880
[Lord Rueang] It might not be
as bad as you think.

1110
01:22:33,840 --> 01:22:36,960
Because the Duke is like a friend
to King Narai.

1111
01:22:40,760 --> 01:22:42,000
That's right, Lady Chanwad.

1112
01:22:57,520 --> 01:22:59,960
Greetings, Lord Pan and Lady Nim.

1113
01:23:00,720 --> 01:23:02,560
What happened to make you gather here?

1114
01:23:03,440 --> 01:23:06,160
The Royal Police took Lord Lek away, Duea.

1115
01:23:09,840 --> 01:23:10,920
It must be Constance.

1116
01:23:12,120 --> 01:23:13,200
Are you sure?

1117
01:23:14,960 --> 01:23:17,240
Who else could it be
except for that lowly westerner?

1118
01:23:19,800 --> 01:23:21,600
It's no surprise
if the King falls on his words.

1119
01:23:22,000 --> 01:23:24,280
However, why does he have to do this
to Lord Lek?

1120
01:23:30,000 --> 01:23:30,840
[Phetracha] Duea.

1121
01:23:31,840 --> 01:23:33,880
Go back to Lord Lek's house.

1122
01:23:35,240 --> 01:23:36,320
Why, Father?

1123
01:23:36,720 --> 01:23:38,400
To ask Lady Nim...

1124
01:23:39,640 --> 01:23:44,320
If Lord Lek took a bribe to advise
against the construction?

1125
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:46,840
It wasn't a bribe, Duea.

1126
01:23:48,200 --> 01:23:49,520
The administrative departments

1127
01:23:51,880 --> 01:23:53,320
gave him a gift.

1128
01:23:59,920 --> 01:24:02,760
His Majesty asked him three times.

1129
01:24:03,520 --> 01:24:07,640
But Lord Lek denied taking
any bribes every time.

1130
01:24:09,240 --> 01:24:10,560
The King didn't believe him?

1131
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:11,920
[Lord Rueang] Yes.

1132
01:24:12,560 --> 01:24:13,800
He didn't believe him.

1133
01:24:15,280 --> 01:24:18,080
A messenger from Lavo took the order
to the Royal Police

1134
01:24:18,760 --> 01:24:20,160
to capture Lord Lek immediately.

1135
01:24:21,680 --> 01:24:22,560
And...

1136
01:24:24,400 --> 01:24:25,800
What is it?

1137
01:24:28,920 --> 01:24:30,640
The King ordered him...

1138
01:24:31,840 --> 01:24:32,680
to be whipped.

1139
01:24:33,840 --> 01:24:34,840
[sighs]

1140
01:24:37,120 --> 01:24:39,120
-How many times?
-One and a half rounds.

1141
01:24:39,200 --> 01:24:40,200
My goodness!

1142
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:42,200
[Horathibodi sighs]

1143
01:24:42,280 --> 01:24:43,960
How many whips is one round?

1144
01:24:46,560 --> 01:24:48,360
One round is 40 times.

1145
01:24:52,480 --> 01:24:53,680
[Lord Rueang] After he is whipped,

1146
01:24:54,240 --> 01:24:58,040
he will be sent home without imprisonment.

1147
01:24:58,760 --> 01:25:00,760
[tense music]

1148
01:25:07,720 --> 01:25:09,720
[tense music continues]

1149
01:25:19,800 --> 01:25:21,800
[somber music]

1150
01:25:29,120 --> 01:25:30,600
[groaning]

1151
01:25:37,160 --> 01:25:38,520
-[sobbing]
-[Lord Lek whimpers]

1152
01:25:51,720 --> 01:25:53,720
[somber music]

1153
01:25:59,640 --> 01:26:01,640
[somber music continues]

1154
01:26:03,960 --> 01:26:05,080
[Nim sobbing]

1155
01:26:18,160 --> 01:26:20,160
[foreboding music]

1156
01:26:46,440 --> 01:26:47,320
Lord Lek.

1157
01:26:49,040 --> 01:26:50,160
[Lord Pan] Lord Lek.

1158
01:26:53,000 --> 01:26:55,400
Was it Constantine Phaulkon?

1159
01:26:58,040 --> 01:26:58,960
[whimpers]

1160
01:27:00,080 --> 01:27:01,560
Don't blame him.

1161
01:27:02,480 --> 01:27:03,840
We don't have any proof.

1162
01:27:09,040 --> 01:27:10,240
[sighs deeply]

1163
01:27:16,760 --> 01:27:18,560
That Phaulkon wanted to be in power.

1164
01:27:22,360 --> 01:27:24,160
It was my fault.

1165
01:27:29,560 --> 01:27:30,520
Pan.

1166
01:27:31,960 --> 01:27:33,720
Why didn't you help him?

1167
01:27:37,800 --> 01:27:40,360
My father is in agonizing pain.

1168
01:27:41,160 --> 01:27:43,160
[foreboding music]

1169
01:27:44,160 --> 01:27:45,000
[Chanwad sobs]

1170
01:27:48,600 --> 01:27:50,600
[tense music]

1171
01:28:26,720 --> 01:28:27,800
Marquess Kosathibodi.

1172
01:28:32,320 --> 01:28:33,640
I read his fortune.

1173
01:28:37,400 --> 01:28:38,800
He won't survive this month.

1174
01:28:39,520 --> 01:28:41,320
[thunder rumbles]

1175
01:28:43,520 --> 01:28:44,560
Oh, no.

1176
01:28:45,520 --> 01:28:47,520
[foreboding music]

1177
01:28:59,360 --> 01:29:01,360
[foreboding music continues]

1178
01:29:21,280 --> 01:29:22,240
[Lord Lek groans]

1179
01:29:24,240 --> 01:29:26,240
[somber music]

1180
01:29:33,360 --> 01:29:34,360
[Lord Lek groaning]

1181
01:29:48,560 --> 01:29:50,120
[water trickles]

1182
01:30:00,520 --> 01:30:01,440
[Lord Lek groaning]

1183
01:30:02,720 --> 01:30:03,720
[Chanwad sniffles]

1184
01:30:23,360 --> 01:30:24,560
Lord Lek.

1185
01:30:25,120 --> 01:30:26,840
-[Lord Lek groaning]
-[Nim sobbing]

1186
01:30:40,760 --> 01:30:41,840
[groans]

1187
01:30:42,920 --> 01:30:44,920
[somber music]

1188
01:30:52,680 --> 01:30:54,680
[somber music continues]

1189
01:31:06,200 --> 01:31:08,040
I deserve this.

1190
01:31:14,960 --> 01:31:16,800
[Nim sobbing]

1191
01:31:30,160 --> 01:31:32,160
[ominous music]

1192
01:31:41,720 --> 01:31:43,520
[George] The head of Treasury is dead,

1193
01:31:44,400 --> 01:31:46,160
just like what we had expected.

1194
01:31:50,360 --> 01:31:51,960
I didn't mean for him to die.

1195
01:31:57,360 --> 01:31:59,360
-[George] It's better that he's dead.
-[sobs]

1196
01:32:01,040 --> 01:32:03,160
[George] Now the power is in your hands.

1197
01:32:05,240 --> 01:32:07,040
I didn't mean for him to die.

1198
01:32:07,400 --> 01:32:08,560
[Phaulkon sniffles]

1199
01:32:09,760 --> 01:32:10,920
I didn't mean that.

1200
01:32:19,880 --> 01:32:21,680
[Chanwad] My father asked me to tell you

1201
01:32:23,840 --> 01:32:28,440
to serve the King
to the best of your ability,

1202
01:32:29,560 --> 01:32:31,960
to live up to his praise for you
to the King

1203
01:32:34,440 --> 01:32:35,760
that you are a talented person

1204
01:32:37,240 --> 01:32:39,720
and you will prosper.

1205
01:32:47,760 --> 01:32:49,760
[somber music]

1206
01:33:22,080 --> 01:33:24,080
[somber music continues]

1207
01:33:48,680 --> 01:33:50,040
-Let's go, Mother.
-[both sobbing]

1208
01:33:54,560 --> 01:33:55,800
[sniffling]

1209
01:34:16,480 --> 01:34:18,480
[ominous music]

1210
01:34:31,560 --> 01:34:33,560
[ominous music continues]

1211
01:34:39,120 --> 01:34:41,120
Was it that westerner who told you

1212
01:34:42,800 --> 01:34:44,920
that Lord Lek received bribes from people?

1213
01:34:46,440 --> 01:34:47,920
Was it, Your Majesty?

1214
01:34:49,880 --> 01:34:50,720
Yes.

1215
01:34:52,120 --> 01:34:53,320
He saw it with his own eyes.

1216
01:34:58,680 --> 01:35:00,040
You believe everything he says.

1217
01:35:02,040 --> 01:35:03,560
[Phetracha] You gave him titles.

1218
01:35:05,880 --> 01:35:07,240
Don't you think that it's like

1219
01:35:09,040 --> 01:35:11,280
you just ordered the execution
of your own brother,

1220
01:35:16,760 --> 01:35:18,960
your trusted warrior,

1221
01:35:22,760 --> 01:35:24,200
someone who would die for you

1222
01:35:28,160 --> 01:35:29,800
just because of him!

1223
01:35:48,560 --> 01:35:49,520
Thongkam.

1224
01:35:53,960 --> 01:35:55,920
Do you think I don't feel sad about this?

1225
01:35:56,560 --> 01:35:57,400
Do you?

1226
01:35:58,760 --> 01:36:00,440
You think I'm such a monster

1227
01:36:00,640 --> 01:36:04,040
that I wouldn't feel anything
when my friend died in front of me?

1228
01:36:05,400 --> 01:36:06,400
Thongkam.

1229
01:36:08,920 --> 01:36:10,200
Let me tell you something.

1230
01:36:12,760 --> 01:36:14,360
I didn't mean for him to die.

1231
01:36:17,800 --> 01:36:19,320
I only punished him

1232
01:36:19,840 --> 01:36:21,800
to set an example.

1233
01:36:22,160 --> 01:36:24,160
[foreboding music]

1234
01:36:30,120 --> 01:36:32,120
[foreboding music continues]

1235
01:36:49,240 --> 01:36:51,240
[men grunting]

1236
01:37:00,080 --> 01:37:02,840
I didn't stay to listen
to what he would have said.

1237
01:37:04,640 --> 01:37:06,560
I didn't want to hear his excuse.

1238
01:37:08,520 --> 01:37:10,960
From now on, I won't waste a second
to think of the benefits

1239
01:37:11,040 --> 01:37:12,880
that western scum brings to Ayutthaya.

1240
01:37:14,680 --> 01:37:17,080
And I won't advise against
any of the decisions.

1241
01:37:19,600 --> 01:37:22,720
I'll wait for the day
when I can't stand it anymore.

1242
01:37:25,400 --> 01:37:27,160
Do you know what day that is?

1243
01:37:28,880 --> 01:37:29,880
I don't, Father.

1244
01:37:31,720 --> 01:37:34,200
It's the day the King falls on his words

1245
01:37:35,400 --> 01:37:37,320
and convert.

1246
01:37:43,040 --> 01:37:44,440
Remember that, everyone.

1247
01:37:48,480 --> 01:37:49,760
Duea, you stay.

1248
01:37:50,320 --> 01:37:51,360
Everybody else can leave.

1249
01:37:59,280 --> 01:38:02,880
[Sorasak] My father gave us an order
to find every way to destroy him

1250
01:38:03,960 --> 01:38:05,880
by using his fraud against him

1251
01:38:06,920 --> 01:38:08,600
or the trading with the British company.

1252
01:38:11,280 --> 01:38:14,160
Soon enough, his wrongdoings
will be revealed somehow.

1253
01:38:14,320 --> 01:38:15,200
[sighs]

1254
01:38:15,760 --> 01:38:17,520
I can't wait that long.

1255
01:38:18,160 --> 01:38:20,160
My father wants to see him demolished
as soon as possible.

1256
01:38:22,680 --> 01:38:24,760
We can start with the British company
he took advantage of.

1257
01:38:26,360 --> 01:38:28,120
I have a man who works for me there.

1258
01:38:28,960 --> 01:38:30,080
It's a good start, Lord Rueang.

1259
01:38:30,720 --> 01:38:32,320
Tell him to gather every intel

1260
01:38:32,480 --> 01:38:34,440
and I'll report to my father,
so he can develop a plan.

1261
01:38:35,520 --> 01:38:37,520
[foreboding music]

1262
01:38:43,320 --> 01:38:45,320
[foreboding music continues]

1263
01:38:48,160 --> 01:38:50,160
[theme music]

1264
01:39:08,200 --> 01:39:09,360
[Mali] Sally.

1265
01:39:22,280 --> 01:39:24,280
[foreboding music]

1266
01:39:32,080 --> 01:39:34,080
[foreboding music continues]

1267
01:39:55,360 --> 01:39:56,280
Master.

1268
01:39:56,880 --> 01:39:57,960
What is it, Clara?

1269
01:40:14,560 --> 01:40:17,760
Madame went
to Marquess Horathibodi's house?

1270
01:40:18,320 --> 01:40:19,360
Clara?

1271
01:40:20,680 --> 01:40:22,040
Yes, Master.

1272
01:40:23,800 --> 01:40:24,720
Are you sure?

1273
01:40:25,440 --> 01:40:26,720
I am, sir.

1274
01:40:31,360 --> 01:40:32,360
Master.

1275
01:40:32,560 --> 01:40:35,440
Go back to your room.

1276
01:40:37,440 --> 01:40:38,560
I told you to leave!

1277
01:40:41,440 --> 01:40:42,280
Go!

1278
01:40:45,160 --> 01:40:46,160
Yes, Master.

1279
01:40:59,400 --> 01:41:00,360
[Phaulkon] Tong Guyomar.

1280
01:41:07,560 --> 01:41:09,240
Please keep this in mind,

1281
01:41:10,640 --> 01:41:13,080
I will be a prominent figure
in this country.

1282
01:41:15,560 --> 01:41:17,960
I will use all of my strength
and wit for it.

1283
01:41:19,520 --> 01:41:21,040
What are you talking about?

1284
01:41:24,800 --> 01:41:28,080
I was promoted to be Earl Rit Kamhaeng

1285
01:41:29,320 --> 01:41:30,960
and I won't stop here.

1286
01:41:32,320 --> 01:41:35,160
I will be the highest-ranking official
of the court.

1287
01:41:35,600 --> 01:41:36,840
And you will see

1288
01:41:37,720 --> 01:41:41,120
who will be greater.
The man you love or me.

1289
01:41:56,200 --> 01:41:57,040
Let's go.

1290
01:41:58,200 --> 01:41:59,160
Tong Guyomar.

1291
01:42:02,720 --> 01:42:04,920
I'm going to prepare a meal for you.

1292
01:42:10,680 --> 01:42:11,560
Damn it.

1293
01:42:12,360 --> 01:42:14,360
[foreboding music]

1294
01:42:21,400 --> 01:42:23,400
[ominous music]

1295
01:42:33,080 --> 01:42:35,080
[ominous music continues]

1296
01:42:50,880 --> 01:42:56,080
Mister Constance
is the official of the Treasury of Siam.

1297
01:42:59,600 --> 01:43:01,920
This is Ayutthaya Warehouse, sir.

1298
01:43:11,320 --> 01:43:13,320
[ominous music]

1299
01:43:18,440 --> 01:43:22,560
They are reviewing the goods
they have just sent.

1300
01:43:23,160 --> 01:43:26,520
The representatives.
Here are all of the records.

1301
01:43:42,640 --> 01:43:44,640
[suspenseful music]

1302
01:44:24,440 --> 01:44:25,440
You take care of that.

1303
01:44:35,120 --> 01:44:36,800
[Lord Rueang] The man
who works for me said that

1304
01:44:36,880 --> 01:44:40,120
their main branch in India
sent their representatives to do an audit

1305
01:44:40,880 --> 01:44:43,480
because of suspicious circumstances
due to their poor sales.

1306
01:44:43,720 --> 01:44:47,120
Hm. It's just like what I said.

1307
01:44:47,680 --> 01:44:50,080
They conspired to steal
from their own company.

1308
01:44:50,880 --> 01:44:51,960
You're right.

1309
01:44:53,800 --> 01:44:55,280
He also said

1310
01:44:56,080 --> 01:44:57,800
they ordered two sets of goods.

1311
01:44:58,800 --> 01:44:59,720
When the goods arrive,

1312
01:45:00,320 --> 01:45:02,240
those two British men
would take them away at once.

1313
01:45:03,400 --> 01:45:04,240
I knew it.

1314
01:45:04,680 --> 01:45:06,120
Though their warehouse is full of goods,

1315
01:45:06,320 --> 01:45:08,520
it couldn't sell out anything

1316
01:45:10,160 --> 01:45:11,880
because people were buying
from these men instead.

1317
01:45:14,880 --> 01:45:16,960
Even if the representatives
found any wrongdoing,

1318
01:45:18,200 --> 01:45:21,680
Constantine Phaulkon wouldn't be at fault.

1319
01:45:22,640 --> 01:45:24,040
The blame will be on those two.

1320
01:45:26,160 --> 01:45:27,240
[sighs]

1321
01:45:28,480 --> 01:45:29,720
It's as you said, Dech.

1322
01:45:31,200 --> 01:45:32,760
If that's the case,

1323
01:45:33,880 --> 01:45:36,320
then how can we put the blame on him,

1324
01:45:36,880 --> 01:45:38,040
this bastard?

1325
01:45:42,240 --> 01:45:44,240
[tense music]

1326
01:45:47,680 --> 01:45:51,760
We have to prove to the British company

1327
01:45:52,880 --> 01:45:55,160
that he is involved.

1328
01:46:05,560 --> 01:46:08,040
I think I know what to do.

1329
01:46:08,520 --> 01:46:10,520
[tense music]

1330
01:46:27,960 --> 01:46:29,960
[tense music continues]

1331
01:46:40,800 --> 01:46:42,800
[foreboding music]

1332
01:46:56,600 --> 01:46:58,600
[foreboding music continues]

1333
01:47:08,560 --> 01:47:10,560
[playful music]

1334
01:47:25,040 --> 01:47:27,040
[playful music continues]

1335
01:47:37,000 --> 01:47:40,040
[Prik] She seemed strange, my lady.

1336
01:47:41,200 --> 01:47:42,760
-How come?
-Hm!

1337
01:47:46,040 --> 01:47:47,600
Like she was sneaking around.

1338
01:47:48,120 --> 01:47:51,680
And her eyes were focused on Lord Dech.

1339
01:47:53,400 --> 01:47:54,560
What was he doing?

1340
01:47:55,400 --> 01:47:56,280
[Prik] Who?

1341
01:47:57,520 --> 01:48:00,480
-My son.
-Well...

1342
01:48:00,680 --> 01:48:06,600
He was pacing back and forth,
then he picked up a book.

1343
01:48:07,960 --> 01:48:09,520
And she watched him do what?

1344
01:48:10,120 --> 01:48:11,560
Well...

1345
01:48:11,720 --> 01:48:17,160
She watched him pacing back and forth,
then picking up a book, my lady.

1346
01:48:19,480 --> 01:48:22,960
What do you want me to do, Prik?

1347
01:48:23,080 --> 01:48:26,920
Hmm. It was inappropriate.

1348
01:48:28,400 --> 01:48:30,120
-Inappropriate?
-[Prik] Yes.

1349
01:48:30,360 --> 01:48:32,560
-Really?
-It is, my lady.

1350
01:48:37,720 --> 01:48:39,720
[foreboding music]

1351
01:48:54,040 --> 01:48:55,080
Are you leaving, son?

1352
01:48:55,880 --> 01:48:56,880
Yes, Father.

1353
01:49:00,320 --> 01:49:01,280
Be careful.

1354
01:49:05,480 --> 01:49:06,320
Muang.

1355
01:49:24,200 --> 01:49:26,200
[tense music]

1356
01:49:44,440 --> 01:49:45,520
-[horse neighs]
-[thwacks]

1357
01:49:45,800 --> 01:49:46,960
-[men yelling]
-[thwacks]

1358
01:49:47,080 --> 01:49:51,000
Would you mind if I come to visit you
from time to time?

1359
01:49:52,120 --> 01:49:54,360
Why did you kill Duke Kosathibodi?

1360
01:49:55,240 --> 01:49:57,400
-I did not do anything.
-Liar.

1361
01:49:57,480 --> 01:49:59,320
[Phetracha] Do you think
you're his favorite?

1362
01:49:59,680 --> 01:50:02,880
Your shadow will be headless soon.
You better watch out.

1363
01:50:02,960 --> 01:50:06,560
-What ceremony do you have in mind?
-Please organize a wedding for me.

1364
01:50:08,080 --> 01:50:09,560
[Karaked's spirit] <i><font color="white">You broke your promise.</font></i>

1365
01:50:10,320 --> 01:50:12,240
[Karaked] <i><font color="white">I'll keep my promise.</font></i>

1366
01:50:12,600 --> 01:50:14,680
<i><font color="white">I won't marry him.</font></i>

1367
01:50:15,320 --> 01:50:18,320
He will still be yours.
[sobs]

1368
01:50:19,880 --> 01:50:21,880
[closing theme music]

1369
01:50:48,200 --> 01:50:50,200

